results.title: Daddy's Fishing Buddy SmartScreen Stencil - Reusable, Adhesive - Tshirts, Canvas, Cards, Glass, Ceramic, Walls, Fabric, Wood, Plastic, Metal
results.description:
Our smart silkscreen stencils are very versatile, self-adhesive, yet easily adjustable AND reusable. Perfect for adding that homemade touch effortlessly. No previous experience required.

This stencil is available in three sizes: A4, A5, and A6 - the image on the stencil is smaller.
Image sizes are as followed: 
A4 stencil = 20 cm by 22.2 cm image | 7.87" by 8.74" image.
A5 stencil = 13 cm by 14.5 cm image | 5.12" by 5.71" image - Only the A5 size stencil comes with the extra design!
A6 stencil = 11 cm by 12.2 cm image | 4.33" by 4.80" image.
Need a different size? Let us know and we'll resize it for you!
All images, except for the first one, are placed on an A4 size background to give you a reference for size. The first image, which is of the large stencil, is 12" by 10" or 304.8 by 254 mm, which is slightly larger than an A4 sheet.
Note: the red and grey text in the images is added to protect copyright and is NOT part of the actual stencil.

NEED A PERSONALIZED STENCIL?

Besides stencils like these, we also make custom stencils. Go to our "Order Custom Stencil" category and click. 
Order your preferred size stencil and send us your design and preferred measurements in a private message through Etsy. 
Not sure which about the size or detail? Just contact us before you order and we will answer any questions you might have.

HOW TO USE YOUR NEW STENCIL:

1. First things first: we HIGHLY recommend turning your stencil over and writing something on the back of the foil the stencil is stuck on with a permanent marker. It doesn't matter what it says, but we write the word "NO" on it. This is to remind you NOT to stick the stencil back onto this side after use. If you do accidentally stick it back onto the wrong side of the clear foil your stencil will get stuck to it. I've done this a few times by accident, try soaking your stuck stencil and carefully peeling it off the foil, trying not to stretch it.
2. Now that you've written on the back of the foil, peel the stencil off it and stick it to a surface of your choice, be it ceramics, fabric, wood, glass, canvas, etc; flat or curved. Apply some pressure to make it stick and avoid getting air bubbles. 
3. Now apply a thin layer of water-based paint evenly over the top with a squeegee or old credit card. A brush can be used, but using strokes only, no dabbing, as bristles may damage small details on the stencil. 
4. Take off the stencil and your print is done! 
5. Make sure to rinse the stencil carefully straight after use to remove any leftover paint before this dries. We do this under running water, you can gently rub the front of your stencil to remove any paint, but do not rub the backside, simple running water should do the trick. Don't use any scrubbing tools or paint remover items as this may ruin your stencil. 
6. Shake off any excess water and place the stencil upside down on a flat surface (like your kitchen counter). Stick the foil back on with the writing facing you. Apply some pressure and remove any air bubbles. Dab off any excess water, flip it over and let it dry. Store it out of sunlight and reuse it! 
Feel free to contact us if you have any questions.

results.description:
You will get an instant download of our “Live Well, Laugh Often, Love Much” printable art. 

No physical item will ship, and the frames shown in the photos are not included.

Our digital designs make decorating your home or office simple. They also make great housewarming, engagement, bridal shower, baby, and wedding gifts!

★ What is a Digital Printable? ★
A high-resolution image file that you purchase, download, and then print as many times as you choose. You are buying a digital download only. No physical prints are shipped.

★ What will you get? ★
You will receive high-quality, print-ready files at 300 dpi resolution in both JPG and PNG. The print sizes are:

* 8x10 inch
* 11x14 inch
* 16x20 inch
* 20x24 inch
* A1 (can also be resized and printed in A2, A3, A4 or A5)

Custom size available upon request.

★ How do I download my printable? ★
As soon as Etsy confirms your payment, you will receive an email with the download link. 

You will always be able to access your files by going to your Etsy Profile -> Purchase and Reviews, and clicking on the “Download Files” link. 

★ Can I request a different size or color? ★
Absolutely! Once you place your order, just send me a message with the size or color you want. For a color change, please let me know the RGB value, if available. I will then email you a link to download your custom file in 1-2 business days. There is no charge for one size change and one color change per order.

★ Can you personalize a design with a name, date, etc.? ★
It’s a definite maybe! Seriously, we can personalize most designs, but not all. Please message us before you order and let us know the design you are interested in buying. We will let you know if we can personalize it.

★ How do I print my art? ★
There are several ways to print your artwork. All are easy!

➤ Home or office printer (most likely limited to 8x10 or 11x14 prints)
➤ Upload or email the file to a local print shop such as FedEx, Staples, CostCo, OfficeDepot, Walgreens, CVS, or many others. You can also transfer the file to a USB drive and bring it to one of these locations.
➤ Upload the file to an online company such as shutterfly.com, mpix.com, or snapfish.com.
Contact a local frame and print shop.

Please let me know if you are having difficulty or if you have any questions.
